vectorData.altText: That's right! Notice that at this level, the cerebral peduncles reaching anteriorly, with the interpeduncular fossa in between them. Notice also a pair of colliculi, posteriorly.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

Many of these features are easily identifiable in MRI. In this image, identify:
the cerebral peduncles reaching anteriorly
the interpeduncular fossa, between them
the cerebral aqueduct 
the colliculi, posteriorly
Some people say a cross section of the midbrain reminds them of Mickey Mouse, his ears being the peduncles. This characteristic shape, with the cerebral peduncles reaching anteriorly, with the interpeduncular fossa in between, and the colliculi located posteriorly identifies the midbrain in MRI.
